---
title: Sweet Chili Chicken Lettuce Wrap with Chicken Thighs, Bell Pepper & Candied Peanuts
description: Our chefs came up with the perfect filling for fresh, crisp romaine leaves: Sautéed ground turkey and bell pepper simmered in a chili-soy sauce, candied peanuts for another layer of crunch, and cilantro for even more green freshness. Get ready to be wowed by the wrap.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6682eb6788a40e5df74250ce-ecf9a234.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/668591149a3c9af871e5c827-en-US.pdf
servings: 2
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 510 kcal
  fat: 23 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 43 g
  sugar: 29 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 970 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 25 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-chili-chicken-lettuce-wrap-668591149a3c9af871e5c827
cuisine: Asian
---

Wash and dry produce.

Core, deseed, and @bell pepper{1}(finely diced). Halve, peel, and finely
dice @onion{1}(finely diced). Trim and discard root end from
@baby lettuce{1}; separate leaves. Quarter @lime{1}. Finely chop
@cilantro{1/4%oz}.

Heat a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add
@peanuts{1/2%oz}, @sugar{1%tsp}, and @water{2%tbsp}. Cook, stirring,
until water has evaporated and peanuts are coated and lightly toasted,
~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in pan used for peanuts
over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and onion; season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until tender and lightly
browned, ~{5-8%minutes}. Transfer veggies to a #plate{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add
@diced chicken thighs{10%oz}; season with salt and pepper. Using a
#spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned
on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}. Break up meat into pieces and cook until
chicken is cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes} more.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Return veggies to pan. Stir in @sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp},
@sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz}, and @butter{1%tbsp}. Cook, stirring,
until mixture is thoroughly coated, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in a squeeze of lime juice to taste.

Divide lettuce leaves between plates; fill with chicken mixture.
Garnish with candied peanuts and cilantro. Serve with remaining lime
wedges on the side.

> TIP: Alternatively, serve chicken mixture, candied peanuts, and
> cilantro in separate bowls and let everyone assemble their own wraps!

> Our chefs came up with the perfect filling for fresh, crisp romaine
> leaves: Sautéed chicken thighs and bell pepper simmered in a
> chili-soy sauce, candied peanuts for another layer of crunch, and
> cilantro for even more green freshness. Get ready to be wowed by
> the wrap.